    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix infinite loop and incorrect position calculation in RWP mobility model\n\n### Summary\nThe Random Waypoint (RWP) mobility model in the OpenAirInterface OMG module had two critical issues:\n\n1. An infinite loop in `update_rwp_nodes()` when processing overdue events due to incorrect time parameter usage\n2. Incorrect position calculation for RESTIRICTED_RWP nodes causing them to jump to wrong positions\n\nThese issues caused the simulation to hang or produce incorrect mobility traces.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/rwp.c`: \n  * Fixed infinite loop in `update_rwp_nodes()` by using correct time parameters and adding loop termination safeguards\n  * Rewrote position calculation logic in `get_rwp_positions_updated()` for RESTIRICTED_RWP type to properly handle Manhattan distance movement\n  * Added division-by-zero protections in position calculations\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a simulation with RWP mobility model using RESTIRICTED_RWP type\n2. Set a high mobility speed and short sleep times to generate frequent events\n3. Run the simulation for an extended period\n4. Observe that the simulation hangs due to infinite loop in event processing\n5. Alternatively, observe incorrect node positions in the mobility traces\n\nThe fix ensures that:\n- Events are processed correctly without infinite loops\n- Node positions are calculated accurately based on their movement model\n- The behavior of `move_rwp_node()` matches the expected Random Waypoint mobility model\n"
}